<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="642" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d642">
                    <head>No. 638.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Fairchild</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-12-02"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 2,
                            1880</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Fairchild</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Minister, Madrid:</hi></p>
                    <p>I am much chagrined that our complaints in regard to the interference by
                        Spanish cruisers with American vessels have produced no result.</p>
                    <p>Ascertain, and telegraph when aswer may be expected.</p>
                    <closer><signed>EVARTS.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>